oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cabinet card photograph of Seaman Second Class Guy E. Housholder
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Seaman 2nd Class Guy E. Housholder of Knoxville, seated on the left, posed before a battleship motif backdrop with an unidentified sailor. He enlisted at age 18 and served on the minelayer U.S.S. Housatonic as a Fireman 2nd Class. He was honorably discharged as an Engineman 2nd Class on August 32, 1919. After the war, he worked as a machinist for the railroad, and died in 1961.
